<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1439: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Marseille</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marseille</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-31">August 31,
                                        1940</date>.<lb/>[Received August 31—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>351. Consulate informed by Commissaire Special at Cerbere Spanish
                                frontier closed. Group of Americans estimated 20 citizens now at
                                Cerbere en route. Barcelona and Lisbon informed. Barcelona wired
                                yesterday frontier situation unclear, apparently now closed to all
                                persons transiting to Portugal. Probably duration situation
                                unknown.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>